#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:5
msgid ""
"The CAPComposer tool is a solution that provides a range of functionalities "
"to support the NMHS in seamlessly issuing CAP. It has been developed with an"
" aim of increasing the adoption of CAP by NMHS in Africa."
msgstr ""
"La herramienta CAPComposer es una solución que proporciona una gama de "
"funcionalidades para ayudar al SMHN a emitir CAP sin problemas. Se ha "
"desarrollado con el objetivo de aumentar la adopción del PAC por parte de "
"los SMHN en África."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:8
msgid "![CAP Example](../../_static/images/cap/cap_example.png \"CAP Example\")"
msgstr ""
"![Ejemplo de CAP](../../_static/images/cap/cap_example.png \"Ejemplo de "
"CAP\")"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:8
msgid "CAP Example"
msgstr "Ejemplo de PAC"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:10
msgid "Some of the key features of the tool include:"
msgstr "Algunas de las características clave de la herramienta incluyen:"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:13
msgid "🌟 Features"
msgstr "🌟 Características"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:15
msgid ""
"Modern user-friendly composer that follows [CAP 1.2](http://docs.oasis-"
"open.org/emergency/cap/v1.2/CAP-v1.2-os.html) standard. Built on top of the "
"awesome [Wagtail CMS](https://wagtail.org)"
msgstr ""
"Compositor moderno y fácil de usar que sigue el estándar [CAP "
"1.2](http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/cap/v1.2/CAP-v1.2-os.html). "
"Construido sobre el increíble [Wagtail CMS](https://wagtail.org)"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:17
msgid ""
"Preview a CAP alert as you edit. Save drafts for sharing with colleagues and"
" collaborating"
msgstr ""
"Obtenga una vista previa de una alerta CAP mientras la edita. Guarde "
"borradores para compartirlos con colegas y colaborar"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:18
msgid ""
"Inbuilt CAP validation. The page will not save if you have not input the "
"required data according to CAP standard"
msgstr ""
"Validación de CAP incorporada. La página no se guardará si no ha ingresado "
"los datos requeridos de acuerdo con el estándar CAP"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:19
msgid ""
"User-friendly alert area map tool that allows multiple ways of constructing "
"alert geographic areas, while keeping the interface simple"
msgstr ""
"Herramienta de mapa de áreas de alerta fácil de usar que permite múltiples "
"formas de construir áreas geográficas de alerta, manteniendo al mismo tiempo"
" la interfaz simple"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:21
msgid "Upload and use your country/territory's administrative boundaries"
msgstr "Cargue y utilice los límites administrativos de su país/territorio"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:22
msgid "Draw a polygon"
msgstr "dibujar un polígono"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:23
msgid "Draw a circle"
msgstr "dibuja un circulo"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:24
msgid ""
"Selecting predefined areas that you create beforehand for common alert areas"
msgstr ""
"Seleccionar áreas predefinidas que cree de antemano para áreas de alerta "
"comunes"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:25
msgid ""
"Inbuilt publishing workflow using Wagtail's powerful page model, with "
"automated emails to composers and approvers"
msgstr ""
"Flujo de trabajo de publicación incorporado utilizando el potente modelo de "
"página de Wagtail, con correos electrónicos automatizados para compositores "
"y aprobadores."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:26
msgid ""
"Collaborate with team members using inbuilt comments (similar to how you "
"could do in Word) with automated notifications. Request for changes and "
"approvals"
msgstr ""
"Colabore con los miembros del equipo mediante comentarios integrados "
"(similar a como podría hacerlo en Word) con notificaciones automáticas. "
"Solicitud de cambios y aprobaciones"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:28
msgid ""
"Publish realtime notifications/messages to third party integrations using "
"MQTT messaging protocol"
msgstr ""
"Publique notificaciones/mensajes en tiempo real para integraciones de "
"terceros utilizando el protocolo de mensajería MQTT"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:29
msgid ""
"Predefine a list of hazards types monitored by your institution, with "
"intuitive icons from [OCHA humanitarian "
"icons](https://brand.unocha.org/d/xEPytAUjC3sH/icons#/humanitarian-icons)"
msgstr ""
"Predefina una lista de tipos de peligros monitoreados por su institución, "
"con íconos intuitivos de [íconos humanitarios de "
"OCHA](https://brand.unocha.org/d/xEPytAUjC3sH/icons#/humanitarian-icons)"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Features.md:31
msgid ""
"Extendable to add your custom logic and functionality. The package provides "
"an `abstract` django model that can be inherited for customizations."
msgstr ""
"Ampliable para agregar su lógica y funcionalidad personalizadas. El paquete "
"proporciona un modelo de Django \"abstracto\" que se puede heredar para "
"realizar personalizaciones."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:1
msgid "CAP Composer and Approver Roles and Publishing Workflows"
msgstr ""
"Funciones de compositor y aprobador de CAP y flujos de trabajo de "
"publicación"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:3
msgid ""
"Within CAP, roles such as \"Composer\" and \"Approver\" are essential to "
"ensure the accuracy and authorization of alerts before dissemination."
msgstr ""
"Dentro de CAP, funciones como \"Compositor\" y \"Aprobador\" son esenciales "
"para garantizar la precisión y autorización de las alertas antes de su "
"difusión."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:5
msgid "**CAP Composer Role:**"
msgstr "**Rol del compositor de CAP:**"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:7
msgid ""
"A CAP Composer is responsible for creating and drafting alert messages. This"
" role involves collecting pertinent information about an incident and "
"structuring it according to the CAP format. The Composer ensures that all "
"necessary details are included to inform the public or specific agencies "
"effectively."
msgstr ""
"Un CAP Composer es responsable de crear y redactar mensajes de alerta. Esta "
"función implica recopilar información pertinente sobre un incidente y "
"estructurarla según el formato CAP. El Compositor se asegura de que se "
"incluyan todos los detalles necesarios para informar al público o a agencias"
" específicas de manera efectiva."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:9
msgid "**CAP Approver Role:**"
msgstr "**Rol de aprobador de CAP:**"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:11
msgid ""
"The CAP Approver reviews the alerts composed by the Composer. This role is "
"crucial for validating the content, ensuring compliance with organizational "
"protocols, and authorizing the release of the alert to the intended "
"audience. The Approver acts as a quality control measure to prevent the "
"dissemination of incorrect or unauthorized information."
msgstr ""
"El Aprobador de CAP revisa las alertas compuestas por el Redactor. Esta "
"función es crucial para validar el contenido, garantizar el cumplimiento de "
"los protocolos organizacionales y autorizar la publicación de la alerta a la"
" audiencia prevista. El Aprobador actúa como una medida de control de "
"calidad para evitar la difusión de información incorrecta o no autorizada."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:13
msgid "**Configuring Composer and Approver Roles**"
msgstr "**Configuración de funciones de compositor y aprobador**"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:15
msgid ""
"The general process for setting up Composer and Approver roles involves the "
"following steps:"
msgstr ""
"El proceso general para configurar los roles de Compositor y Aprobador "
"implica los siguientes pasos:"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:17
msgid "**Access the User Management or Administration Section:**"
msgstr "**Acceder a la Sección de Gestión o Administración de Usuarios:**"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/Composer-and-Approver.md:18
msgid ""
"Navigate to the system's settings where users and groups are managed.  "
"![Users and Groups](../../_static/images/settings/users_and_groups.png "
"\"Users and Groups\")"
msgstr ""
